@@TJvMousePositionner
Description:
This component is usefull for positionning the mouse cursor to a specific position of the screen, or on a control. The cursor will move smoothly to the new position. (Like if the user was moving the mouse).

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMousePositionner.FControl

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMousePositionner.Execute@Integer@Integer
Description:
Use this method to center the mouse cursor on the control specified in the control property.

Parameters:
Steps: 
is the number of steps in the animation.
Delay: 
is the delay between each step of the animation.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMousePositionner.ExecuteEx@TPoint@Integer@Integer
Description:
Use this method to center the mouse cursor on the a specific point on the screen.

Parameters:
Dest: 
is the destination of the cursor.
Steps: 
is the number of steps in the animation.
Delay:
is the delay between each step of the animation.

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
@@TJvMousePositionner.Control
Description:
This property is the control you want to use when calling the execute method. When calling the execute method, the cursor will be centered on this control.

